derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English (earlier than vincible): via Old French from Latin invincibilis, from in- 'not' + vincibilis (see vincible)

entry.tran: 不可战胜的;所向披靡的
entry.def: If you describe an army or sports team as invincible, you believe that they cannot be defeated.

example.ex: When Sotomayor is on form he is virtually invincible.
example.tran: 索托马约尔状态好时几乎无人可敌。

entry.tran: (信念、态度)不可动摇的，不可改变的
entry.def: If someone has an invincible belief or attitude, it cannot be changed.

example.ex: He also had an invincible faith in the medicinal virtues of garlic.
example.tran: 他同时也对大蒜的医学功效深信不疑。
